trees.description: The root of this tree.  The title of this node sets the title of the tree.  You must have one tree called "Root".  You can set tree-wide properties on this node and reference them in other places with the following template syntax: `{{key_name}}`.

63756788-9049-48ab-afef-948bf34a69b3.description: An action that calls the function specified in the title (must be in valid Elixir terms).  The title can contain "template variables" (like `{{mod}}.rename({{new_name}}, true)`) which will be replaced with corresponding values looked up on the parent tree.

b818c29a-4426-4ac4-9e9d-2e365b6870d1.description: Takes multiple children and runs them from top to bottom (or left to right), succeeding when any one succeeds.  Fails if all fail.
